4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING DEFINITIONS RELATED TO PARTNER
5 OR FAMILY MEMBER ASSAULT; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS OF "BODILY INJURY" AND "REASONABLE
6 APPREHENSION OF BODILY INJURY"; AMENDING SECTION 45-5-206, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
7 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10 Section 1. Section 45-5-206, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "45-5-206. Partner or family member assault -- penalty. (1) A person commits the offense of
12 partner or family member assault if the person:
13 (a) purposely or knowingly causes bodily injury to a partner or family member;
14 (b) negligently causes bodily injury to a partner or family member with a weapon; or
15 (c) purposely or knowingly causes reasonable apprehension of bodily injury in a partner or family
16 member.
17 (2) For the purposes of Title 40, chapter 15, 45-5-231 through 45-5-234, 46-6-311, and this
18 section, the following definitions apply:
19 (a) "Bodily injury" means:
20 (i) a cut, abrasion, bruise, burn, or disfigurement;
21 (ii) physical pain; or
22 (iii) temporary illness or impairment of the function of a bodily member, organ, or mental faculty.
23 (a)(b) "Family member" means mothers, fathers, children, brothers, sisters, and other past or present
24 family members of a household. These relationships include relationships created by adoption and remarriage,
25 including stepchildren, stepparents, in-laws, and adoptive children and parents. These relationships continue
26 regardless of the ages of the parties and whether the parties reside in the same household.
27 (b)(c) "Partners" means spouses, former spouses, persons who have a child in common, and
28 persons who have been or are currently in a dating or ongoing intimate relationship.
