1 (vii) a forfeiture of bail or collateral deposited to secure the defendant's appearance in court in this
2 state or in another state for a violation of a statute similar to this section, which forfeiture has not been vacated.
3 (4) (a) An offender convicted of partner or family member assault is required to pay for and
4 complete a counseling assessment with a focus on violence, controlling behavior, dangerousness, and
5 chemical dependency. An investigative criminal justice report, as defined in 45-5-231, must be copied and sent
6 to the offender intervention program, as defined in 45-5-231, to assist the counseling provider in properly
7 assessing the offender's need for counseling and treatment. Counseling providers shall take all required
8 precautions to ensure the confidentiality of the report. If the report contains confidential information relating to
9 the victim's location or not related to the charged offense, that information must be deleted from the report prior
10 to being sent to the offender intervention program.
11 (b) The offender shall complete all recommendations for counseling, referrals, attendance at
12 psychoeducational groups, or treatment, including any indicated chemical dependency treatment, made by the
13 counseling provider. The counseling provider must be approved by the court. The counseling must include a
14 preliminary assessment for counseling, as defined in 45-5-231. The offender shall complete a minimum of 40
15 hours of counseling. The counseling may include attendance at psychoeducational groups, as defined in 45-5-
16 231, in addition to the assessment. The preliminary assessment and counseling that holds the offender
17 accountable for the offender's violent or controlling behavior must meet the standards established pursuant to
18 44-7-210 and be:
19 (i) with a person licensed under Title 37, chapter 17, 22, or 23;
20 (ii) with a professional person as defined in 53-21-102; or
21 (iii) in a specialized domestic violence intervention program.
22 (c) The minimum counseling and attendance at psychoeducational groups provided in subsection
23 (4)(b) must be directed to the violent or controlling conduct of the offender. Other issues indicated by the
24 assessment may be addressed in additional counseling beyond the minimum 40 hours. Subsection (4)(b) does
25 not prohibit the placement of the offender in other appropriate treatment if the court determines that there is no
26 available treatment program directed to the violent or controlling conduct of the offender.
27 (5) In addition to any sentence imposed under subsections (3) and (4), after determining the
28 financial resources and future ability of the offender to pay restitution as provided for in 46-18-242, the court
