1 shall require the offender, if able, to pay the victim's reasonable actual medical, housing, wage loss, and
2 counseling costs.
3 (6) In addition to the requirements of subsection (5), if financially able, the offender must be
4 ordered to pay for the costs of the offender's probation, if probation is ordered by the court.
5 (7) The court may prohibit an offender convicted under this section from possession or use of the
6 firearm used in the assault. The court may enforce 45-8-323 if a firearm was used in the assault.
7 (8) The court shall provide an offender with a written copy of the offender's sentence at the time of
8 sentencing or within 2 weeks of sentencing if the copy is sent electronically or by mail."
